oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Income Comparisons
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Heider, L. E.
Donham, J. C.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Prior to July, 1967, we were conducting our dairy practice in a manner that I have arbitrarily defined as traditional service. We received calls from our clients and performed the service the same day with a minimal amount of pre-arranged scheduling. Our fee system for this service I have also arbitrarily defined as traditional. We charged a base call fee plus a professional fee which was frequently based on the cost of drugs and equipment and, to some extent, on the type of service performed.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: American Association of Bovine Practitioners Conference Proceedings; 1972; 2-4
